The paper focuses on the use of creativity in requirements elicitation within Agile Software Development, which falls under the software engineering (cs.SE) category. Additionally, the paper discusses the importance of user engagement and user interface development, which are relevant to the human-computer interaction (cs.HC) category. The paper also mentions specific agile methodologies such as Scrum and Extreme Programming, which are relevant to the software development (cs.SD) category. The paper also discusses the benefits and limitations of these approaches, which are relevant to the cybernetics (cs.CY) and computer engineering (cs.CE) categories.
